HEADWORD: Bryopsida
<hw>Bryopsida</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>the class of plants comprising the
true mosses, having leafy rather than thalloid gametophytes; it
comprises the orders <ord>Andreaeales</ord>; <ord>Bryales</ord>;
<ord>Dicranales</ord>; <ord>Eubryales</ord>; and
<ord>Sphagnales</ord>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> class <class>Bryopsida</class>, Musci, class
<class>Musci</class>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bryozoa</ent>⟦br⟧
